# lupilup — Cursor Rules & Agent Guidelines

> This file is read automatically by Cursor. Follow these rules in every response.
> Do not ask clarifying questions covered here — just apply the rules.

---

## 1. Project overview

lupilup is a mobile yarn organiser app for knitters and crocheters.
Domain: lupilup.app
Target audience: English-speaking, primarily Ravelry users.
Goal: replace Ravelry's desktop-only stash management with a beautiful mobile-first experience.

**Legacy names:** In older prompts and docs, *KnitKeep* / *Knitkeeper* refers to this same product (lupilup). Treat them as equivalent.

---

## 2. Tech stack

| Layer | Technology | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Framework | React Native + Expo (SDK 52+) | File-based routing via Expo Router |
| Language | TypeScript (strict mode) | No `any`, no untyped callbacks |
| Styling | NativeWind v4 | Tailwind classes in React Native |
| Backend | Supabase | Auth, PostgreSQL, Storage |
| AI Vision | Google ML Kit | Local OCR only |
| AI Logic | Gemini 1.5 Flash | Label parsing, cloud only |
| External API | Ravelry API | Read-only, OAuth 2.0 |
| Navigation | Expo Router v3 | File-based, typed routes |

---

## 2b. Git workflow

- Never start a new feature from an old working branch.
- Before any new feature or fix: switch to `main`, pull the latest `origin/main`, then create a new feature branch from that updated `main`.
- Never commit directly to `main`.
- Do not reuse yesterday's branch for today's task, even if the scope feels related.

---

## 3. Folder structure

```
/app
  /(auth)
    login.tsx
    magic-link.tsx
  /(onboarding)
    ravelry-import.tsx
  /(tabs)
    stash.tsx
    projects.tsx
    _layout.tsx
  index.tsx                 ← splash / auth gate

/components
  /ui                       ← generic: Button, Input, Card, Badge
  /stash                    ← YarnCard, StashList, FilterPills
  /projects                 ← ProjectCard, PatternReader, FinishModal
  /scanner                  ← ScannerCamera, ConfirmSheet, DuplicateWarning

/lib
  supabase.ts               ← Supabase client singleton
  ravelry.ts                ← Ravelry API helpers
  gemini.ts                 ← Gemini API helpers
  units.ts                  ← metric/imperial conversion helpers
  yarn.ts                   ← yarn business logic (blend formula etc.)

/constants
  colors.ts                 ← design tokens
  fonts.ts
  config.ts                 ← env vars, API endpoints

/hooks
  useAuth.ts
  useStash.ts
  useYarnCard.ts
  useScanner.ts

/types
  yarn.ts
  project.ts
  user.ts
```

